Sentencas: The fabrication of a cathode layer of solid oxide fuel cells by the dispenser printing was investigated and found to be useful in the creation of a thicker ceramic layer using viscous ceramic slurries.
Titulo: Application of dispenser printing for the preparation of a SOFC cathode with controlled microstructure

Sentencas: The cathode layer prepared from a mixture of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-delta (LSCF) and Ce0.9Gd0.1O1.95 (GDC) slurry clearly shows an inhomogeneous microstructure which leads to poor cell performance.
Titulo: Application of dispenser printing for the preparation of a SOFC cathode with controlled microstructure

Sentencas: In order to solve this problem, the size of the LSCF particles was controlled through a milling process.
Titulo: Application of dispenser printing for the preparation of a SOFC cathode with controlled microstructure

Sentencas: Better cell performance was observed for the cells with controlled microstructure by adjusting the pore former content, the LSCF/GDC ratio, in addition to the particle size control.
Titulo: Application of dispenser printing for the preparation of a SOFC cathode with controlled microstructure

Sentencas: This process might be useful in the deposition of a thick ceramic layer on a curved substrate such as micro-tubular cell.
Titulo: Application of dispenser printing for the preparation of a SOFC cathode with controlled microstructure
